Some Engen service stations might see a shortage of 50ppm diesel over the next few days. CAPE TOWN - Contingency plans have been put in place to mitigate a shortage of a certain grade of diesel in the Western Cape.Some Engen service stations might see a shortage of 50ppm diesel over the next few days.Engen's Gavin Smith explains the shortage is a result of difficulties being experienced by a supplier in the region. We expect sporadic supply challenges of 50ppm diesel. This may see some our service stations intermittently experience shortages of the product. Our customers remain our first priority and we apologise for any inconvenience caused. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)